b'A woman who showed me the truest definition of unconditional love. She passed away peacefully in her sleep and even blessed us with one final Mother\xe2\x80\x99s Day which she enjoyed to the fullest.\n\nHamba Kahle Gogo. \xe2\x9d\xa4\xef\xb8\x8f'

b'I know many of you grew to love Gogo from afar and I thank you for the condolences and the blessings you\xe2\x80\x99ve sent in her memory. I\xe2\x80\x99ve cried all week celebrating the greatest \xe2\x80\x9cmovie\xe2\x80\x9d I\xe2\x80\x99ve ever watched. A story that began with my first breath and ended with her last.'
b'a place where everyone was guaranteed to feel the love emanating from her mighty chest.'

b'Her house in Soweto wasn\xe2\x80\x99t just a home, it was a refuge, a place where other women would come when they had no other place to go, a place where members of the community would gather to pray together every single week\xe2\x80\xa6'

b'My grandmother was born in 1927 and even though she was 95 years old, she still had the best memory of us all.  Every moment spent with her felt like a magical journey through time where she would recount all of the family\xe2\x80\x99s greatest joys, losses, achievements and milestones.'
